VThere have been many revolutions over the last century,
p4
aVbut perhaps none as significant as the longevity revolution.
p5
aVWe are living on average today 34 years longer
p6
aVthan our great-grandparents did \u2014 think about that.
p7
aVThat's an entire second adult lifetime
p8
aVthat's been added to our lifespan.
p9
aVAnd yet, for the most part,
p10
aVour culture has not come to terms with what this means.
p11
aVWe're still living with the old paradigm
p12
aVof age as an arch.
p13
aVThat's the metaphor, the old metaphor.
p14
aVYou're born, you peak at midlife
p15
aVand decline into decrepitude.
p16
aa(lp17
V(Laughter)
p18
aa(lp19
VAge as pathology.
