aa(lp21
VBut many people today \u2014 philosophers, artists, doctors, scientists \u2014
p22
aVare taking a new look at what I call "the third act" \u2014
p23
aVthe last three decades of life.
p24
aVThey realize that this is actually a developmental stage of life
p25
aVwith its own significance,
p26
aVas different from midlife as adolescence is from childhood.
p27
aVAnd they are asking \u2014 we should all be asking:
p28
aVHow do we use this time?
p29
aVHow do we live it successfully?
p30
aVWhat is the appropriate new metaphor for aging?
p31
