aa(lp136
VFor me, it began as I was approaching my third act, my 60th birthday.
p137
aVHow was I supposed to live it?
p138
aVWhat was I supposed to accomplish in this final act?
p139
aVAnd I realized that, in order to know where I was going,
p140
aVI had to know where I'd been.
p141
aVAnd so I went back and I studied my first two acts,
p142
aVtrying to see who I was then,
p143
aVwho I really was, not who my parents or other people told me I was,
p144
aVor treated me like I was.
p145
aVBut who was I?
p146
aVWho were my parents \u2014 not as parents, but as people?
p147
aVWho were my grandparents?
p148
aVHow did they treat my parents?
p149
aVThese kinds of things.
